:QUOTE
Scope is the enemy of shipping. A working MVP beats a perfect roadmap.

:INFO
Solo SaaS in 30 Days
A time-boxed framework for solo founders to scope, build, and launch a software product in one month. The goal is a paying customer, not a finished product.

:COUNTER.half
30 Days
Hard deadline from idea to live product
|
:COUNTER.half
3 Features
Maximum scope for a viable MVP

:PATH
Week 1
Define the problem, target customer, and one-sentence value proposition. Build a landing page and start collecting email signups before writing code.

:PATH
Week 2
Build the core feature loop. Use existing libraries and no-code for everything that is not your differentiator. Ship to five beta users.

:PATH
Weeks 3 and 4
Collect feedback, fix critical bugs, add payment via Stripe, and do a public launch on Product Hunt or Hacker News Show HN.

:CHECKLIST
30-Day Launch Checklist
[ ] Write problem and solution statement
[ ] Identify three potential first customers
[ ] Build landing page with waitlist
[ ] Define MVP feature scope (max three features)
[ ] Set up Stripe before building features
[ ] Ship to beta users by day 14
[ ] Collect and act on one round of feedback
[ ] Launch publicly by day 30

:NOTE
Charge from day one. Free users give you activity but not signal. A customer who pays 10 dollars per month has a completely different relationship to the product than one using it for free.